column14: Q uncertainty 7.33% with largest source velocity 7.06%. Elected to do mmnt section at gauge as u/s had water flowing over ice. Due to ice effect u/s mmnt x-section had majority of panels with large angle warnings. Negative Q panels also exist due to ice effect and are valid. Boulders throughout mmnt section.  Tech in creek chipping out location for water cut and mmnt cross-section 0857-0921PST (hence jump in water levels during this time frame). Did first water cut after chipping out ice and sensor had stabilised. Elected not to purge due to sub-zero water temps and stable sensor. Sensor resets varied pre and post mmnt (mmnt done at gauging location and oline my have been disturbed?) Sensor reset of 0.006m (sensor reset to 1.506m) at 1214PST.
